a:5:{s:5:"title";s:72:"Membrain adds multiple phone numbers and Phone Tags to contact records";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:1469:"<p>Membrain released a contact data update aimed at better reflecting how sales teams handle phone details in practice. The change introduces two capabilities: storing more than one number per contact and tagging each number for clarity and filtering.</p>
<h3>What’s new</h3>
<p>1) Multiple phone numbers per contact<br />
Contacts can now store several phone numbers (mobile, direct, office, older numbers, etc.) without overwriting existing data. Membrain says this also helps teams keep context and see which phone number was used in previous calls.</p>
<p>2) Phone Tags for labeling and segmentation<br />
Each phone number can be labeled with Phone Tags such as Direct, Mobile, Active, or Do not use (and custom tags). The tags are designed to be actionable: teams can use them for segmentation and filtering.</p>
<h3>Practical use cases mentioned</h3>
<ul>
<li>Find contacts with an active direct number</li>
<li>Exclude do not use numbers from outreach</li>
<li>Keep contact phone data cleaner over time</li>
</ul>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>Single phone fields don’t match real B2B sales data, especially as teams scale and contact details change. By allowing multiple numbers with structured tags, Membrain is making phone data more usable for day-to-day selling as well as reporting and segmentation.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://www.membrain.com/product-updates">https://www.membrain.com/product-updates</a></p>
